f:\mathbb{R}^2\to\mathbb{R}, f(x,y)=(x^2+y^2)^2-8(x^2-y^2).
f
X=\{(x,y):f(x,y)\leq 0\}
(x,y):\nabla f(x,y)=0.
\displaystyle\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}= 4x(x^2+y^2)-16x, \displaystyle\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}= 4y(x^2+y^2)+16y
\displaystyle\frac{\partial f}{\partial x}=\displaystyle\frac{\partial f}{\partial y}=0
4x[(x^2+y^2)-4]=0,4y[(x^2+y^2)+4=0]\implies (x,y)=\{(0,0),(-2,0),(2,0)\}
X
x=\rho\cos\theta,y=\rho\sin\theta
(x,y)\in X \iff r^4-8r^2\cos2\theta\leq0 \iff \frac{1}{8}r^2\leq\cos2\theta
\displaystyle\int_0^{\pi}\displaystyle\int_0^{2\sqrt{2\cos2\theta}}\rho\;d \rho d\theta?.
\displaystyle\int_0^{\pi}\displaystyle\int_0^{2\sqrt{2\cos2\theta}}\rho\;d \rho d\theta=4\displaystyle\int_0^{\pi}\cos2\theta\;d\theta=2\sin2\theta|_{\theta=0}^{\theta=\pi}=0
